# ========================================
TC-AMS-SUBMIT-01

SUMMARY
AMS R1 Submit - Successfully Submit All Responded AMS Notifications (Artificial Surface)

DESCRIPTION
Verifies the complete AMS Round 1 submit journey for a farmer or agent who has responded to all Red parcel notifications. The test covers pressing Submit, verifying the Submit confirmation popup content, confirming submission via Yes button, verifying the green toast message, verifying the response PDF is generated with the correct edit map Y/N indicator, and verifying the Farmer Dashboard AMS panel updates to show the green tick. Also verifies the AgriSnap message appears only when rejections exist, downstream effects on Land Details and Internal screens for accepted, rejected, and deleted parcels, and the internal history note. Linked to Xteams 4918 for EOS integration.

LABELS
AMS, Submit, Round1, ArtificialSurface, EOS, TestOnly

COMPONENT
AMS - Submit Process - Round 1

ENVIRONMENT
CENTEST

ROUND
Round 1 - 2026

TEST DATA

Run on CENTEST_BISS_DATA - Find herd with all AMS responses saved but not yet submitted:
select LVL_HERD_NO, LML_PARCEL_LABEL, a.* from vwbs_ams_response a where lvl_year = 2026 and lvl_submit_id is null and ams_round = 1 order by lvl_herd_no;

Run on CENTEST_BISS_DATA - Find herd with AMS Admin Inspection Round 1:
SELECT app_herd_no, app_year, ist_desc, ins_completion_date, int_abbrev, int_desc FROM vwbs_inspection WHERE app_year = 2026 AND int_abbrev = ‘A’ ORDER BY app_herd_no;

Run on CENTEST_BISS_INET - Get agent login for herd:
SELECT hbcus.bcus_bus_id AS HERDNO, (SELECT ui.uri_username FROM tdcr_user_info ui WHERE uri_ccs_bus_id = abcus.bcus_bus_id AND ROWNUM = 1) AS USERNAME FROM tdco_customer_asscs ca, tdco_business_customers abcus, tdco_business_customers hbcus WHERE SYSDATE BETWEEN ca.ca_start_date AND ca.ca_end_date AND ca.ca_cac_code = 194 AND ca.ca_bcus_id_from = abcus.bcus_id AND ca.ca_bcus_id_to = hbcus.bcus_id AND hbcus.bcus_bus_id = ‘<HERD_NUMBER>’ ORDER BY ca.ca_start_date DESC;

PRECONDITIONS

- Herd has Red AMS findings in Round 1
- All Red parcel responses have been saved (accepted, rejected, or withdrawn/deleted)
- At least one rejection exists for the AgriSnap message sub-scenario
- At least one accepted response with map edit exists for digitising task sub-scenario
- At least one deleted parcel exists for the deletion sub-scenario
- Agent login resolved via INET query

