# ========================================
TC-AMS-SUBMIT-02

SUMMARY
AMS R1 Submit - Submit Blocked When Not All AMS Responses Completed

DESCRIPTION
Verifies that when a farmer or agent attempts to submit AMS Round 1 responses before all Red parcel notifications have been responded to, the system correctly blocks submission and displays a red validation message. Each unresponded parcel must show a red symbol on the row. The Accept/Reject findings column must show Select option in red for unresponded parcels. The Submit button must not proceed and a clear red error message must inform the user they must complete all responses first.

LABELS
AMS, Submit, Validation, Round1, TestOnly

COMPONENT
AMS - Submit Process - Validation

ENVIRONMENT
CENTEST

ROUND
Round 1 - 2026

TEST DATA

Run on CENTEST_BISS_DATA - Find herd with AMS findings (partial responses):
select * from VWBS_AMS_NOTIFIED_HERD where scheme_year = 2026 and expired = 0 order by herd_no;

Run on CENTEST_BISS_INET - Get agent login:
SELECT hbcus.bcus_bus_id AS HERDNO, (SELECT ui.uri_username FROM tdcr_user_info ui WHERE uri_ccs_bus_id = abcus.bcus_bus_id AND ROWNUM = 1) AS USERNAME FROM tdco_customer_asscs ca, tdco_business_customers abcus, tdco_business_customers hbcus WHERE SYSDATE BETWEEN ca.ca_start_date AND ca.ca_end_date AND ca.ca_cac_code = 194 AND ca.ca_bcus_id_from = abcus.bcus_id AND ca.ca_bcus_id_to = hbcus.bcus_id AND hbcus.bcus_bus_id = ‘<HERD_NUMBER>’ ORDER BY ca.ca_start_date DESC;

PRECONDITIONS

- Herd has multiple Red AMS findings in Round 1
- At least one parcel has been responded to and at least one has NOT been responded to
- Agent login resolved via INET query

STEPS

