# ========================================
TC-AMS-SUBMIT-05

SUMMARY
AMS R1 Submit - Accept Response with Claimed Area 0.00 ha Submits Successfully and EOS Receives Correct Data for All Response Types

DESCRIPTION
Verifies that a claimed area of 0.00 ha is accepted by the system when saving and submitting an AMS Accept response. EOS must receive 0.00 ha correctly. Also verifies that EOS receives the correct data for each individual response type - one accept, each of the five reject reasons individually (Bare soil, Crop is as claimed, Feature no longer exists, Temporary bale storage, Other with free text), and withdrawn parcels. Linked to Xteams 4918 EOS integration. Also verifies AMS Response PDF generation handles fewer than 4 rounds in 2025 as per the technical note requiring change of PDF generation logic.

LABELS
AMS, Submit, AcceptResponse, ClaimedArea, EOS, Round1, TestOnly

COMPONENT
AMS - Submit Process - EOS Integration

ENVIRONMENT
CENTEST

ROUND
Round 1 - 2026

TEST DATA

Run on CENTEST_BISS_DATA - Find herd with AMS findings:
select * from VWBS_AMS_NOTIFIED_HERD where scheme_year = 2026 and expired = 0 order by herd_no;

Run on CENTEST_BISS_DATA - Find AMS crop mismatch herds for reject reason testing:
select apl.app_year, apl.app_herd_no, apl.parcel_id, apl.crp_desc AS application_crop, ams.crop_found_eos AS ams_crop_found FROM vwbs_application_land apl LEFT JOIN vweo_ams_inspected_land ams ON apl.apl_lnu_id = ams.lnu_id AND apl.app_herd_no = ams.inspected_herd AND apl.app_year = ams.scheme_year WHERE apl.app_year = 2026 AND apl.mde_abbrev = ‘I’ AND apl.apl_deleted_ind = ‘N’ AND apl.app_herd_no = ‘<HERD_NUMBER>’;

Run on CENTEST_BISS_INET - Get agent login:
SELECT hbcus.bcus_bus_id AS HERDNO, (SELECT ui.uri_username FROM tdcr_user_info ui WHERE uri_ccs_bus_id = abcus.bcus_bus_id AND ROWNUM = 1) AS USERNAME FROM tdco_customer_asscs ca, tdco_business_customers abcus, tdco_business_customers hbcus WHERE SYSDATE BETWEEN ca.ca_start_date AND ca.ca_end_date AND ca.ca_cac_code = 194 AND ca.ca_bcus_id_from = abcus.bcus_id AND ca.ca_bcus_id_to = hbcus.bcus_id AND hbcus.bcus_bus_id = ‘<HERD_NUMBER>’ ORDER BY ca.ca_start_date DESC;

PRECONDITIONS

- Herd has Red AMS findings in Round 1
- Separate herds available to test each reject reason type individually
- Agent login resolved via INET query

